            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Ok let's try it.\r\n\r\n> Not directly, but it also doesn't indicate that it's not allowed.\r\n\r\nJust in general, in any case of ambiguity, we must always favour the lowest-common-denominator for the widest support. If a server doesn't have to support a zero-rootdir config with multiple documents, then we should never assume/require it. I guess this is exactly why lspconfig had `single_file_support`.\r\n\r\nHowever, since we had this behaviour before it should be safe enough to revert to it for now.",
